31/10/2005
ANKARA, Turkey -- Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan said on Friday (28 October) that he expects progress to continue in Turkey's EU integration process after Austria takes over the rotating EU presidency from Britain early next year. During an informal meeting of the EU ministerial council in London Friday, Erdogan described relations with Austria as good.
In other news Friday, a soldier and a Kurdish militant were killed in a battle in Turkey's Sirt province. Four other troops were injured when Kurdistan Workers Party (PKK) terrorists opened fire on an army post. 
Meanwhile, six suspected PKK members have been arrested in connection with the bombing of a petrol station in Istanbul. Five people were wounded in the 15 October attack. (AFP - 29/10/05; NTV - 28/10/05)
